#: ../../E/EXCH.rst:5
msgid "EXCH"
msgstr "EXCH"

#: ../../E/EXCH.rst:7
msgid "/eks´ch\\@/, /eksch/, vt\\."
msgstr "/eks´ch\\@/, /eksch/, 他動詞"

#: ../../E/EXCH.rst:9
msgid ""
"To exchange two things, each for the other; to swap places. If you point to "
"two people sitting down and say \"Exch! \", you are asking them to trade "
"places. EXCH, meaning EXCHange, was originally the name of a PDP-10 "
"instruction that exchanged the contents of a register and a memory location."
" Many newer hackers are probably thinking instead of the :ref:`PostScript` "
"exchange operator (which is usually written in lowercase)."
msgstr ""
"二つのものを、それぞれ互いに交換すること。場所を入れ替えること。座っている二人を指して「Exch!」と言えば、二人に場所を入れ替えるよう頼んでいることになる。EXCHは、EXCHangeの意味で、元々はレジスタとメモリ位置の内容を交換するPDP-10の命令の名前だった。多くの新しめのハッカーは、おそらく代わりに\\"
" :ref:`PostScript`\\ のexchange演算子(通常は小文字で書かれる)のことを思い浮かべるだろう。"
